<h2>Solar Incentives in Los Angeles</h2>
<p>Los Angeles residents have access to multiple solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal Investment Tax Credit provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, then steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. California's Self-Generation Incentive Program (SGIP) offers rebates for solar-plus-storage systems, providing up to \$1,000 per kWh of battery storage capacity. LADWP customers can benefit from the utility's net energy metering program, which credits solar customers at retail rates for excess electricity sent back to the grid. Additionally, Los Angeles County offers property tax exemptions for solar installations, ensuring that adding solar panels won't increase your property tax assessment despite increasing your home's value.</p>

