<p>When selecting a solar installer in Los Angeles, prioritize companies with proper California Contractor's State License Board (CSLB) licensing, specifically C-46 solar contractor licenses. Look for installers with extensive local experience, as they'll understand LA's permitting processes, LADWP interconnection requirements, and optimal panel positioning for the region's sun patterns. Top-tier companies offer comprehensive warranties including 25-year panel performance guarantees, 10-12 year equipment warranties, and workmanship warranties of at least 10 years. Verify that installers are NABCEP-certified and check reviews on platforms like Better Business Bureau, Google, and Solar Reviews. Request multiple quotes and ensure each proposal includes detailed production estimates based on your roof's orientation, shading analysis, and Los Angeles's specific solar irradiance data.</p>

